4.53/5  rDev +1.1%look: 4 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.5Pour is pitch black with a small caramel-colored head. The head leaves no lacing as it dissipates but settles into a nice golden ring around the top of the beer. 
The aroma brings loads of sweet milk chocolate, vanilla, and roasted coffee beans, with just a touch of alcohol. Just the faintest hint of chili peppers are lurking in the background, giving a nice little tingle to the nostrils. 
The flavor has a ton of coffee up front, followed by a wave of sweet milk chocolate and faint vanilla. Finishes slightly charred, with a subtle touch of spicy chili peppers. 
The feel is full bodied with lower carbonation. Incredibly rich and smooth. Has a fair amount of alcohol warmth and lingering heat from the chili peppers. 
Overall, a fantastic imperial stout that really brings out the flavors and aromas it advertises. I'm not a fan at all of chili peppers in beer but it's done very subtly here and adds a nice spicy character to the beer without detracting from the coffee, chocolate, and vanilla. Just an excellent stout. 1,030 charactersScaryEd, Jun 22, 2016
