4.74/5  rDev +5.8%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 4.75 |  overall: 4.756/9/16, Adding to 11/2015 review. Had several bottles and now on draft.
Looks like an imperial stout, though not motor oil like some. Some sparse foam rings the glass. Looks a bit flat (but it isn't).
Nose is big coffee, dark fruit, burnt sugar
Taste follows the nose, roasty coffee, but with more chili spice, a little dark chocolate, some brown sugar sweetness on the sides of the tongue. Sweetens up as it warms, but never gets cloying.
Mouthfeel is oily slick, hot and a little prickly but somehow not off-putting in any way, it works. The chili's give the impression of taking up the cause for the scorch, and not the alcohol, so it just feels right. 
Drier than some big stouts, very balanced sweet, spicy, smoky, bitter. All around just a deeply complex and quaffable imperial stout. Want a comparison? KBS with chilies - all the way. 845 charactersdoucmehu, Nov 08, 2015
