4.25/5  rDev -5.1%look: 4.25 | smell: 4.25 | taste: 4.25 | feel: 4.25 |  overall: 4.25Pours a deep and slick motor oil black with a surprisingly sturdy finger of light khaki foam.
Strong aroma of chocolate, coffee, vanilla, roast, and a subtle hint of spice.
Sticky sweet chocolate and vanilla flavor accompanied by bitter coffee and roasted malts, the sweetness is settled out by the subtle spiciness that washes over the tongue on the back end of the sip to prep the palate for another sip.
Heavy-bodied, medium carbonation, rich, smooth, and slightly spicy.
Overall, I am not generally a fan of the use of chili peppers in beers, but this was very well put together. In my experience, most brewers go crazy with the peppers and the spice overpowers everything else, but the heat that accompanies this brew is subtle and enjoyable. 751 characterslarryarms847, Aug 23, 2015
