4.5/5  rDev +0.4%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.5Pours an appetizing pitch-black, with a rich brown head and very persistent lacing.
Smell is a chocolatey, coffee-laden spice bomb; aromas of cinnamon, red pepper, nutmeg, and allspice.
Taste is absolutely awesome: chocolate, coffee, roasted grains and malt duel with red pepper and spices: cinnamon, nutmeg, allspice, and grains-of-paradise are distinguishable. Rich dark-fruit flavors of prunes, raisins, and cherries fight through more spice on the mid-palate, with yet more spices, chocolate, and coffee on the finish.  Mouthfeel is appropriately rich, with spot-on, creamy carbonation. Of all the flavored stouts I've had, this might well be the best. 658 charactersVikingBeer, Aug 22, 2015
