4.71/5  rDev +5.1%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.75Pours perfect stout color, fizzy head of loose carbonation fades nearly immediately.
Nose is chocolate and coffee with hint of vanilla - all there.  Peppers don't come through on the nose for me.
Basically a perfect balance on the flavors here - so damn impressive.  Peppers add a perfect level of heat and compliment what sweet there is so well.  
This is a touch thinner than I'd have expected and I think that's to its benefit.  It's an incredibly drinkable stout with all that's going on - can't believe it's a 13% (compare to a BCBS at 14% that is booze+).  Awesomely delicate - very impressed with this.  Glad I snagged a few to hold on to for the cooler months.
Edit:  I had about 6 of these and noticed that the pepper started to drop off much faster than anticipated.  As that balance was one of my favorite aspects and it dissipated quickly over a matter of weeks I dropped my initial score on both taste and feel 1/4 point from my initial review. 961 charactersoldn00b, Aug 14, 2015
