4.93/5  rDev +10%look: 4.75 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 5 | feel: 5 |  overall: 5This made a cross country trip with me from San Diego (Bottlecraft) to Western PA. Poured into the snifter. Absolutely pitch and devoid of light, with the thinnest ring of khaki head. Definite alcohol legs on this baby. Aromas of chocolate (and such deep, rich, REAL chocolate), very subtle vanilla, some alcohol sweetness that reminds me of Kahlua,  dark roast coffee all at a very cold 40 degrees from the fridge. More vanilla working around as the glass warms. The flavors on this were immense. TONS of chocolate and coffee crashing like waves over my palate. Again subtle vanilla, and after a few sips I began to notice a slight warmth from the chiles. Vanilla and chiles (which can be overpowering flavors) were used with a very restrained hand. Big coating mouthfeel. One sip remained on my palate for what seemed like an eternity. Warmed up my chest after a few sips. This beer is an absolute monster, and the best stout that I have tried... possibly the best beer/beer experience I have tried. This bomb blew the hype out of the water, and stood tall. If you can find it, try it. 1,087 charactersMikus, Jul 01, 2015
