4.65/5  rDev +3.8%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.75Poured into a balloon glass.
Look: Midnight black with a creamy mocha colored head that resides to a thick film. Nice lacing initially.
Aroma: Dark roasted malts, rich cocoa, and ancho chili peppers bring some nasal-clearing heat. Very subtle vanilla sweetness in the middle.
Taste: First of all, the peppery heat from the ancho chills is absolutely perfect -- not too hot, but enough to sense it. A very dark chocolatey beginning with a lot of roasted malts. A sweeter vanilla middle gives way to the heat of ancho chilis. The finish is a bit chalky with a cocoa aftertaste.
Mouthfeel: Smooth, creamy.
Overall: A perfect blend of ingredients with a perfect amount of heat. Alcohol is almost undetectable. Delicious sipper. 728 charactersJuicesFlowing, Mar 08, 2015
