4.5/5  rDev +0.4%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.5Got this on a trade and it seemed very interesting.
A - Pours a dark brown and settles into a deep black with a small brown colored head with moderate lacing.
S - Rich aroma with roast, chocolate and coffee. Some sweet malt, vanilla, and alcohol is also present. 
T - The roastiness from the smell is first but closely accompanied by the rich cocoa, malt, and coffee tones. Again the traditional stout flavors are then changed in the middle by the unique ingredients of the chilies and the vanilla. There is just so much going on in this beer it is difficult to pick out all that is going on in one sip. The finish has some alcohol and a bitter finish. I didn't pick up any spice from the chili.
M - Big mouth-feel. low carbonation. Overall balanced but slightly cloying and the flavors just stick to the palate.
Overall, this is a very good imperial stout. This beer has a ton of novel flavors including the chilies and the vanilla but overall it almost makes it muddled for my palate trying to pick out the flavors that are trying to come together. I did very much enjoy this beer but I feel that there are better tasting stouts out there.
Glass- Snifter 1,162 charactersdmgeng, Feb 15, 2015
