4.68/5  rDev +4.5%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 4.75 |  overall: 4.75No bottle date
Look - Pours black as midnight and completely opaque.  Nice head with a tan cappuccino color.  Bubbles range from very tiny to medium sized.  Excellent lacing.  
4.5 paws.
Smell - Delicious rich coffee aroma.  A nice subtle chili spice is present as well.  Dark chocolate reveals itself the more I smell.  Very inviting.  4.5 paws.
Taste - Intense coffee and subtle chili flavor up front with velvety chocolate coming through on the finish.  The vanilla gets lots amidst all the robust flavors, but does provide a smoothing balance.  There is a bit of a woody character present as well.  Bitter finish, not sure if it is provided by the hops or coffee/cocoa nibs.  Quite delicious.  4.75 paws.
Feel - Smooth and creamy, mild tingle on the tip and sides of tongue.  The chili spice is very noticeable on the lips.  4.75 paws.
Overall - I've been wanting to try this one for a long time, and it did not disappoint.   I love stouts with chocolate and chilies and this is one of the best.  Always nice to have a beer that lives up to the hype.  4.75 paws. 1,071 charactersBowWowWowYippyYoIPA, Feb 07, 2015
