A  looks black enough, deep cola edge, two fingers of mocha head quickly cuts itself in half than retains fairly well leaving lots of random lace, some wide legs after a swirl once everything fell 
S  heavy on the chocolate and coco, faint vanilla, lots of coffee, more chocolate, I normally don't get much pepper in chilli stouts but I'm picking it up in this one, it is what it claims in a big way
T  less chocolate and the coffee really come out to play, some char, faint licorice, not much vanilla, still has some chilli going on, burnt espresso rinds as it airs out, I have no idea where the 13% is hiding
M  not as thick as I'd guess but there's enough bubbles to fluff it up a little, a little oily on the palate, very little heat for such a strong beer but some faint chilli heat, and heavy coffee and char linger strong for ages 
O  the hypes real with this one, the adjuncts they use are hard to miss and work well together and the booze is nearly invisible, fairly impressive for a biggin 
I'm not sure if I want to age this on as its drinking great fresh, the coffee works well and I'm not sure if I'd want it to fade, not much booze fresh either, oh well I'll find out anyways because I'm stocking up 1,258 characterswordemupg, Jan 11, 2015
