4.39/5  rDev -2%look: 4 | smell: 4.25 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.25 |  overall: 4.5Pale orange wax. Chico1985 picked this up for me in Oklahoma City some months ago. Been in the fridge since. Full notes and review last night onto PC.
A- Pitch black, thick oily body poured from the stubby to a wine glass; well actually four. A small tan head rises up to half a finger or so with a frothy texture. A very small ring remains and lacing is mostly spotty.
S- Very roasty and pretty much burnt grains dominate the nose with an espresso/super dark coffee feel as well. Vanilla sweetness helps to buffer the roastiness just a bit but it certainly is a bomb of roast malts. Veggie pepper hint comes into play later on.
T- For me, this is one of the most roasty and charred grain brews I have ever had. The finish pretty much defines black with a barrage of espresso, coffee bean, chocolate, ash and heavily toasted nuts. The peppers are quite flavorful but only a bit of heat on the back end. Vanilla dessert feel on the back end rounding it all out.
MF- Thick bodied with a fairly chewy and creamy consistency. Carbonation is at a fairly high level for the style but the texture takes the edge off of it. Finishes warm from the peppers and with an intense roast bitterness.
Lots of huge flavors brought to the table here and somehow they end up working out together. Chiles are flavorful and a bit warm and integrate smoothly with the massive espresso and sweet vanilla at the end. This is my kind of dessert. Also, insanely roasty... like burnt in a good way. 1,476 characterscbutova, Nov 16, 2014
