4.64/5  rDev +3.6%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 4.25 |  overall: 4.5Date: 10/31/14
Location: Halftime Mamaroneck
Draught/Bottle: Bottle
Glassware: Snifter
Appearance: Black until it's edging where it reaches a very dark brown. Mocha colored one inch head on a regular pour without much retention. Slight alcohol viscous cling very little carbonation cling. 
Aroma: A power blend of ancho peppers, spicy, mildly hot bordering on freshly vegetal, with a rich coffee not overly bitter but roasted, vanilla and sweet cocoa. 
Taste: The coffee is the first flavor on my tongue as I get a nice roasting, followed by the peppers which taste almost like sweet peppers. At the end I get a light chocolate to help with the spice and some vanilla. 
Mouthfeel: Medium to Med high in body which is surprising. I would have thought this beer needed to have more heft to carry the weight if it's ingredients. Medium carbonation. The best part of the beer is how the ancho warms the tongue and the back of the throat after the beer has been swallowed. 
Notes: 977 charactersKornWallace, Nov 01, 2014
