4.75/5  rDev +6%Poured from bottle into snifter.
A- Dark black and very thick.  Tiny khaki head that quickly disappeared.  Very mild carbonation and lacing present.
S-  Lots of coffee and mocha on the nose.  Smooth smell of vanilla milkshake mixed in and lots of toasted oats and malts.  Smells like a delicious dessert with a side of caffeine.  Not much smell of the peppers.
T-  As the nose indicates, there's a good amount of coffee, expresso, and chocolate up front.   The coffee and chocolate is followed by sticky molasses and smokey, burnt malts.  All of this turns into a beautiful light heat down the throat from the peppers and booziness.
M-  Very full bodied and creamy.  The stickiness compliments the dryness of this stout, much like the sweetness compliment the heat.  Very little carbonation and I let mine hit almost room temp so it rolled right over the tongue leaving plenty of flavor behind.
O-  Possibly the best coffee, cocoa, and pepper stout I've had to date.  The flavors are all bold and complex, but come together perfect on the aftertaste.  This one comes highly recommended and is another winner from Prairie Artisan.  Just wish I had an endless supply for the colder months. 1,192 charactersEveningCordial, Oct 29, 2014
