4.54/5  rDev +1.3%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.25 |  overall: 4.5Thanks to @Narthax for a great trade.
A - We have ourselves a spent motor-oil coloration and consistency and a dark tan head that, even with a vigorous pour, gives way pretty quickly with only a bit of lacing. 
S - The nose on this bastard is bracing, with more than the chocolate/coffee/soy sauce mélange one expects from imperial stouts. The base aroma is similar to Oskar Blues’ Ten Fidy or Bell’s Expedition Stout (two beers I love) but it’s wrapped in cigar smoke and leather, butterscotch, honey and mesquite. 
T - An intense espresso and cherry cordial flavor with a fair amount of dark chocolate, figs and roasted black marshmallow. Bomb! is sweet, yes, but not saccharine. And the burn from those ancho chilis cauterizes any lingering sugar, leaving only a delightful coffee ground aftertaste. 
M - The weight is definitely heavy, but manageable for a stout this robust. Also boozy as hell, which makes me happy that it's distributed in 12 oz. bottles.
This is a wonderful Mayan stout, though it doesn't unseat Mexican Cake as my all-purpose touchstone of the style. Nonetheless, I'm keeping my eyes open for this the next time I'm in the OK/TX area. 1,171 charactersTheCuriograph, Oct 02, 2014
