4.5/5  rDev +0.4%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.5Original rating updated on 2/26/2017: 
This is a review of an orange waxed bottle, released January 2014 - so about 3 years old at this point. 
First off I must say, despite BOMB!'s ubiquity around here I haven't had this beer since probabaly around the time I bought this bottle.  Just a bit over the top and rich for what I want to drink on a regular basis. Generally, I'm not big on "adjunct flavors" in my beer and certainly not multiple adjuncts in the same beer. That said, it's always been a solid beer - but at three years this has really mellowed to be really easy and enjoyable to drink.
Chocolate and vanilla stand front and center now, creamy and smooth. No bitterness from either hops or roasted grain is left, yet it's not sweet either. Chile heat is gone but a subtle warm toasted flavor persists.  Complexity comes from layers of flavor that include, burnt sugar, molasses, tobacco, and coffee. Impressively, for both an old and big beer, the foam stays dense through the whole glass.
I've been holding on to this for no real reason and decided to open it for no real reason. Glad I did, and I suspect the gold waxed I bottle I still have won't be around long. 1,180 charactersbump8628, Jan 15, 2014
