4.37/5  rDev -2.5%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.25 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 3.75 |  overall: 4.5Poured on tap at Churchkey into a snifter glass.
Real good looker, presented with a decent one finger collar, dark mocha brown with creamy bubbles and whipped up top. Good staying power, on a super dark walnut black body, eventually a thin collar sticks around which is quite dark as well. Impressive.
Nose is perfect roasted coffee, ripping beans going on here, lots of char and nuts strangely. For as much as there are other items added such as peppers, nibs and vanilla those are very buried. But a very KBS like bouquet here.
First thing on the first sip is that the beer is very light, even a bit fizzy surprisingly. However the flavors just jump and take over. Large piping dark roasted coffee, some slight sweetness that's a bit indistinct. Great pepper like action that comes out nice and black with the charring malted roasts, even a faint bit of somkey quality also. There is no heat on this at all for it's large fourteen percent body.
Really impressive and diverse beer, that is going to please any stout fan. Just wish this had a bit more body to it, but it's hard to believe this clocks in at such a high abv to match. KBS killer is a possibility. 1,165 characterssmakawhat, Nov 19, 2013
