5/5  rDev +11.6%look: 5 | smell: 5 | taste: 5 | feel: 5 |  overall: 5Prairie Artisan Ales - Prairie Bomb
Imperial Stout 
14% ABV
Appearance - Darker than black. Take your normal black and then bold it. Thin dark khaki head.
Smell - Roasted cocoa with some vanilla to help balance the alcohol.
Taste - Sheer perfection! The chili works to activate your taste buds, which then receive the ccocoa, vanilla, and roasted espresso. The alcohol is prevalent, but works perfectly to balance the explosion of flavor. If there is a better stout available, I haven't found it. Prairie Bomb is destroying all competition with this product.
Mouthfeel - Extremely thick and creamy (even for an imperial stout).
This is my favorite beer on the planet. It's a must find for every stout connoisseur. 718 characterscapnamerica, Aug 18, 2013
