4.82/5  rDev +7.6%look: 4.5 | smell: 5 | taste: 5 | feel: 4 |  overall: 4.75MammothTarantula, Jun 02, 2013
4.79/5  rDev +6.9%look: 4.75 | smell: 5 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.75Poured into a tulip glass.
Appearance - Stout dark with a fairly decent-sized tan head. The beer leaves great lacing and alcohol legs on the glass. 
Aroma - Huge, inviting, complex aroma. Up front, I got a sweet chocolate note, along with roasted malt, coffee, and some vanilla. The chili pepper note is a bit hidden in the background, but still noticeable. 
Taste - There is a lot going on here. The taste is bold and complex. The chocolate note is less pronounced than it was in the nose, but still up front. The dark roasted malt flavor is fantastic, and complements the other flavors. The coffee is very present as well, as is the vanilla. There are also interesting, fruity and tobacco-like notes that I can't quite explain. Chili peppers become apparent at the backend, and leave a pleasing heat on the tongue.
Mouthfeel- It's medium bodied, but a bit thinner than I expected (think BA Old Rasputin). However, it coats the mouth and leaves a strong, pleasant aftertaste, accentuated by the mild chili pepper heat. 
Overall - This is an extremely solid stout, and is the best PAA beer I've had to date (which is saying a lot). It's incredibly smooth and flavorful, and really hides its 14% ABV. With so much going on, beers like this risk being unbalanced. However, here, the flavors all complement one another and all are expressed adequately. I can't wait to see how this ages. 1,389 charactersBuster, Jun 01, 2013
